    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix display_channelmodel function to show complete channel information\n\n### Summary\nThe `display_channelmodel()` function in the random channel simulation tool was not displaying all relevant fields from the channel descriptor structure. This made debugging channel models difficult as important parameters like model name, center frequency, and correlation level were missing from the output.\n\nAdditionally, there were minor formatting issues in the display output with typos in field labels.\n\nThis fix enhances the `display_channelmodel()` function to show all important channel parameters and fixes the formatting issues.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/SIMULATION/TOOLS/random_channel.c`: Enhanced `display_channelmodel()` function to display additional channel parameters and fixed formatting typos.\n\n"
}